text.section:
A supervised individual on a higher level of supervision shall presumptively be placed on administrative supervision if he or she has:
Completed twelve (12) months of community supervision;
Not violated the terms of his or her community supervision in the previous twelve (12) months;
Fulfilled all restitution and other financial obligations to the court;
Demonstrated a reduction in criminal risk factors upon reassessment; and
Achieved the goals established in his or her case plan.
